{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FcGA6ED8WPxbTS4TE3BjwZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me generate my comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of `cloche list` Command Implementation and Related Code\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition for `list`\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 75-76, 104, 217-261)\n\nThe `cmdList` function is defined and handles:\n- Takes `--all` flag to list all runs (otherwise defaults to last hour)\n- Calls `client.ListRuns(ctx, &pb.ListRunsRequest{All: all})`\n- Outputs formatted table with: RunID, WorkflowName, State, Type (host/container), Title, ContainerID, ErrorMessage\n\nCurrent output format (line 241-259):\n```\nRunID  WorkflowName  State    Type        Title  ContainerID  ErrorMessage\n```\n\n**Current behavior:**\n- No project filtering at CLI level\n- No `--project` flag currently exists\n- Project directory is available via `os.Getwd()` at line 152 (in `cmdRun`)\n\n### 2. gRPC Service Definition\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 12, 90-107)\n\n**Service Definition:**\n```proto\nrpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n\nmessage ListRunsRequest {\n  bool all = 1;\n}\n\nmessage ListRunsResponse {\n  repeated RunSummary runs = 1;\n}\n\nmessage RunSummary {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string workflow_name = 2;\n  string state = 3;\n  string started_at = 4;\n  string error_message = 5;\n  string container_id = 6;\n  string title = 7;\n  bool is_host = 8;\n}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** `RunSummary` does NOT include `project_dir` field (only has 8 fields)\n\n### 3. Domain Types for Run\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 31-47)\n\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState\n  ActiveSteps    []string\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  StartedAt      time.Time\n  CompletedAt    time.Time\n  ProjectDir     string        // <-- PROJECT FIELD EXISTS!\n  ErrorMessage   string\n  ContainerID    string\n  BaseSHA        string\n  ContainerKept  bool\n  Title          string\n  IsHost         bool\n  ParentRunID    string\n}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** Domain `Run` has `ProjectDir` field, but it's NOT exposed in proto `RunSummary`\n\n### 4. Store/Port Interfaces for Listing Runs\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 10-19)\n\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n  CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n  GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n  UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n  DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n  ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n  ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)  // <-- EXISTS!\n  ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)  // <-- EXISTS!\n  ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- `ListRunsByProject()` interface already exists in the port\n- `ListProjects()` interface already exists in the port\n- These methods are designed for multi-project filtering\n\n### 5. Daemon Handler for List Requests\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 387-411)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n  var since time.Time\n  if !req.All {\n    since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)\n  }\n  runs, err := s.store.ListRuns(ctx, since)  // <-- Only calls ListRuns, not ListRunsByProject!\n  if err != nil {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n  }\n\n  resp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n  for _, run := range runs {\n    resp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n      RunId:        run.ID,\n      WorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n      State:        string(run.State),\n      StartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n      ErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n      ContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n      Title:        run.Title,\n      IsHost:       run.IsHost,\n      // NOTE: ProjectDir is NOT included in RunSummary!\n    })\n  }\n  return resp, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** The handler doesn't use `ListRunsByProject()` - only calls `ListRuns()`\n\n### 6. SQLite Store Implementation\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 224-241, 243-260)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error) {\n  // Filters by project_dir with optional since parameter\n  // Returns runs ordered by state (running first) then started_at DESC\n}\n\nfunc (s *Store) ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error) {\n  // Returns all DISTINCT project_dir values from runs table where project_dir != ''\n  // Ordered alphabetically\n}\n```\n\nDatabase schema includes: `project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''` column in runs table (line 74)\n\n### 7. Project Detection Logic\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 152, 379, 444-445, 528)\n\nExisting project detection patterns:\n- **cmdRun:** Uses `cwd, _ := os.Getwd()` then passes as `ProjectDir` to gRPC\n- **cmdLoop:** Uses `cwd, _ := os.Getwd()` and passes as `ProjectDir` to gRPC\n- **cmdTasks:** Uses `filepath.Base(cwd)` to extract just directory name for project label\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1623-1645)\n\n```go\nfunc projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n  // Builds mapping from full paths to short labels\n  // Uses filepath.Base() for single-component paths\n  // Uses parent/base for disambiguation when multiple projects share same base name\n}\n```\n\nWeb handler uses `ListRunsByProject()` with full directory paths at multiple locations (lines 199, 261, 495, 538, 779, 1035)\n\n### Key Architecture Findings\n\n1. **Multi-Project System Exists:**\n   - Database stores `project_dir` for each run\n   - `ListRunsByProject()` and `ListProjects()` methods exist in the store interface\n   - Web dashboard already shows project filtering with project labels\n\n2. **CLI/gRPC Gap:**\n   - The CLI `list` command doesn't expose project filtering\n   - The gRPC proto `RunSummary` doesn't include `project_dir` field\n   - The gRPC handler only calls `ListRuns()`, not `ListRunsByProject()`\n\n3. **Project Path Handling:**\n   - Full absolute paths stored in `project_dir` (e.g., `/home/user/workspace/myproject`)\n   - Web layer converts full paths to short labels for display\n   - CLI `tasks` command already uses `filepath.Base(cwd)` for project identification\n\n4. **Existing Store Methods (Complete):**\n   - `ListRuns(ctx, since)` - all runs\n   - `ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, since)` - runs filtered by project\n   - `ListProjects(ctx)` - all distinct project directories\n   - `ListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID)` - runs under a parent run\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths for Reference:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI implementation\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC definitions\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Domain Run type\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Store interface\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC handler\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite implementation\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web dashboard (shows working project filtering)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a67a9980537862609 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60814\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 51589</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d13e2ce4-0d07-448e-8673-06ba707df971","uuid":"da1c6f3f-f4da-411f-b8d4-a0af28cc004b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the `cloche list` command implementation and related code. Please find:\