{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Akp1pYuDCMxVs9wy3w7faj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No curl, wget, or ability to install protoc. I'll need to manually edit the generated proto Go files. This is a bit tricky but doable. I need to:\n\n1. Update the `.proto` file (for documentation/future regeneration)\n2. Manually add `ProjectDir` field to `ListRunsRequest` in the generated Go code\n3. Manually add `ProjectDir` field to `RunSummary` in the generated Go code\n4. Update the raw descriptor bytes (this is the tricky part)\n\nActually, the raw descriptor bytes are used for reflection and registration. If I modify the Go structs but not the descriptor, the protobuf reflection won't know about my new fields. \n\nBut here's the real issue: gRPC relies on Protocol Buffers binary serialization, and both client and server need to agree on the schema. If I add fields to the Go structs without updating the proto descriptor, the server won't be able to deserialize the incoming messages correctly since it won't recognize the field numbers in the binary encoding.\n\nThe safest approach is to regenerate the protobuf code using the Go plugins rather than trying to manually add fields.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":175,"cache_read_input_tokens":49910,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":175},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d13e2ce4-0d07-448e-8673-06ba707df971","uuid":"746d8b45-faec-4e99-be0f-4ef7c0413ca7"}
